ogdl.template

Class ComplexPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • ogdl.support.Parser
      • ogdl.template.ComplexPath
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Template

    public class ComplexPath
extends Parser
    This class parses a string and produces a graph. The string should contain a path expression as per the following rules: cpath = element (dot element)* note: a dot is optional before and after cqualifier and group. element = word | quoted | cqualifier | group cqualifier = ('[' | '{') expr (']' | '}') group = '(' expr ( (space|comma) expr)* ')' expr = [op1] (path|group|number|quoted) (op2 [op1] (path|group|number|quoted) )* kword = 'true'|'false'|'null' are readed as paths.
